title: Google\Cloud\GkeMultiCloud\V1\AzureDatabaseEncryption
name: AzureDatabaseEncryption
description:
Configuration related to application-layer secrets encryption.

Anthos clusters on Azure encrypts your Kubernetes data at rest in etcd using Azure Key Vault.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.gkemulticloud.v1.AzureDatabaseEncryption

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.key_id
params.description: Required. The ARM ID of the Azure Key Vault key to encrypt / decrypt data. For example: /subscriptions/<subscription-id>/resourceGroups/<resource-group-id>/providers/Microsoft.KeyVault/vaults/<key-vault-id>/keys/<key-name> Encryption will always take the latest version of the key and hence specific version is not supported.
